We see that the Hartree-Fock approximation is based on an independent particle model. The major problem that arises from Hartree's initial assumption is due to the fact that the wavefunction is not antisymmetric in both spin and spatial coordinates in accordance to the interchange of any two electrons. This of course is prohibited due to the effect of the Pauli exclusion principle which is expressed by the following statement,
